channel.title: What's going on in your life MoparScape?
channel.description:
I haven't posted a topic in here for a while and I haven't seen a post-worthy topic in a while (jmo).
Anyways, what's happening in everyone's lives? You call talk about school, making new friends, hobbies or really anything you think is relevant to post.
I'll start off. I'm starting college tomorrow (August 26th) at Tennessee Tech University and I plan to major in Computer Engineering. I'm looking for a job where I live to pay for school and I hope I can find a good balance of school/job/girlfriend/hobbies if you have any suggestions on time management feel free to post. I haven't been hopelessly browsing the internet like I used to, I've found better activities to do than to always sit at my computer. I haven't played any video games in months aside from a bit of UMvC3 and some classic Cod4.
Anyways, post away!

item.dc:creator: @jal_knight jal knight
item.description:
@jal_knight wrote:

Cres:

It wouldn’t mean a thing but it’s better off this way. It’s annoying more than anything else. I’m more worried about the job <_<

Good way of looking at it Keep your head up!

I started working for Sprint Customer Care and it is the most mental fking job I’ve ever had… Customers call in all day and tell you how big of a POS you and and you agree with them…lol
Getting married June 14th so I’m having too work some overtime in order to make sure we can pay for it plus the honeymoon. I told her McDonald’s would be a perfect honey moon but she said she would divorce me?
In about 2-3 months we will be looking for a house with a bank loan so I’m pretty excited about that. I’ve been living in an apt for about 2 years and were growing out of it.
Recently got the Xbox back so I’ve been playig some FC3, DP3 and a little of assasins creed 3… Other than that life is decent and living one day at a time.

item.title: What's going on in your life MoparScape?
item.dc:creator: @Cres Cres
item.description:
@Cres wrote:

My crush broke up with me after a week… In the first part of this summer I was mainly depressed because of that, usually drinking my sorry ass up because of that.
I learned a little more Java, C and Assembly this summer when I wasn’t depressed. I blocked the girl from fb because she said she still loved me but apparently didn’t hesitate to kiss a guy when she was on vacation in Turkey. Bought a book to get my driver’s license but haven’t really looked into it. I applied everywhere to get a job and I finally got one; I only have to work saturdays for 8 hours and I get paid €330/month. Today I’ve been having stings on the area of my lungs again, which means they probably partially collapsed (I smoked some weed with friends… shouldn’t have done that)… If I don’t show up next weekend I may lose my job and school starts again next monday so I’ll have to face that girl again (unless I’ll be in the hospital for my lungs… great)

So yeah… fun stuff
